# Pre-Installation AI Security Ruleset

This directory contains the **rule definitions** for the AI Security Checker pre-installation phase. Before any pre-trained AI model (HuggingFace, Ollama, LM Studio) is permitted to run in an enterprise environment, the checker runs a pipeline of scans and evaluates results against this ruleset. Each rule has an **action** (BLOCK, WARN, or AUDIT) that determines whether installation is blocked, allowed with acknowledgment, or only logged for compliance.

## How a checker uses this ruleset

The rules are consumed by the **AI Security Checker** described in [../ai_security_checker_implementation_plan.md](../ai_security_checker_implementation_plan.md). The checker:

1. Loads all YAML files under `pre-installation/rules/` (one file per rule).
2. Runs scanner modules (serialization, malware, HuggingFace API, license engine, Garak, etc.) that produce **findings** keyed by `rule_id`.
3. For each finding, looks up the rule by `rule_id` and applies its **action** (BLOCK / WARN / AUDIT).
4. A single **BLOCK** finding halts the pipeline and denies installation; WARN requires explicit acceptance; AUDIT is logged only.

Rule metadata (severity, remediation, frameworks) is used for reporting (SARIF, HTML, SIEM) and for override/policy logic.

## Rule categories and training data focus

Rules are grouped by **category** (directory under `rules/`). The following categories directly address **what data the model was trained on** and **security issues in training data** for pre-trained models:

| Category | Rule prefix | Focus |
|----------|-------------|--------|
| **data-provenance** | AI-DP | Training data sources, web scrapes, AI-BOM availability |
| **identity** | AI-ID | Model card, training data section, uncensored/jailbroken naming, version pinning |
| **privacy** | AI-PD | PII scrubbing, memorization risk for large models |
| **behavior-alignment** | AI-BA | Safety evaluation, Garak ASR, benchmarks (HarmBench, TruthfulQA) |
| **regulatory** | AI-RC | GDPR (EU personal data in training), EU AI Act, export control |

Other categories cover **supply chain and integrity** (can we trust this artifact?), **licensing**, and **infrastructure**:

| Category | Rule prefix | Focus |
|----------|-------------|--------|
| code-execution | AI-CE | Pickle/malware, trust_remote_code, malicious deps |
| supply-chain | AI-SC | Typosquatting, namespace hijacking, signing, provenance |
| model-format | AI-MF | Safetensors vs pickle, GGUF Jinja2 template risk |
| licensing | AI-LC | No license, AGPL, CC BY-NC, Llama/Gemma/Mistral, AUP |
| infrastructure | AI-IR | Ollama binding/version, NVIDIA container, VRAM, seccomp, rate limiting |

