| AI-IR-003 | NVIDIA Container Toolkit below 1.17.4 | BLOCK | infrastructure |
| AI-MF-001 | Pickle format when safetensors alternative exists | WARN | model-format |
| AI-MF-002 | GGUF contains Jinja2 chat template (SSTI risk) | WARN | model-format |
| AI-MF-003 | High-risk format (.ckpt, .joblib, .dill) | WARN | model-format |
| AI-SC-003 | Publisher is not a verified HuggingFace organization | WARN | supply-chain |
| AI-SC-004 | No signed commits on model repository | WARN | supply-chain |
| AI-SC-005 | Fine-tune of unknown or unverified base model | WARN | supply-chain |
| AI-ID-001 | Model card missing or incomplete | WARN | identity |
| AI-ID-002 | Uncensored or unfiltered in model name or tags | WARN | identity |
| AI-LC-004 | Llama Community License — check MAU threshold | WARN | licensing |
| AI-LC-005 | Gemma Terms — synthetic data license propagates | WARN | licensing |
| AI-LC-006 | Mistral MNPL/MRL — non-commercial only | WARN | licensing |
| AI-BA-001 | Fine-tuned with no safety evaluation documentation | WARN | behavior-alignment |
| AI-BA-002 | Garak attack success rate exceeds 15% threshold | WARN | behavior-alignment |
| AI-DP-001 | Training data includes unfiltered web scrapes | WARN | data-provenance |
| AI-PD-001 | Model over 7B parameters with no documented PII scrubbing | WARN | privacy |
| AI-IR-004 | Model VRAM exceeds available GPU memory | WARN | infrastructure |
| AI-IR-005 | Inference container lacks seccomp or AppArmor | WARN | infrastructure |
| AI-ID-003 | Model card present but training data section empty | AUDIT | identity |
| AI-ID-004 | Model version not pinned (pull by name not hash) | AUDIT | identity |
| AI-LC-007 | License has acceptable use restrictions | AUDIT | licensing |
| AI-LC-008 | Base model license differs from derivative | AUDIT | licensing |
| AI-RC-001 | High-risk EU AI Act classification possible | AUDIT | regulatory |
| AI-RC-002 | Possible GPAI transparency obligations | AUDIT | regulatory |
| AI-RC-003 | Training data may contain EU personal data | AUDIT | regulatory |
| AI-RC-004 | US export control review may be required | AUDIT | regulatory |
| AI-DP-002 | No AI-BOM available for this model | AUDIT | data-provenance |
| AI-BA-003 | Behavioral benchmarks not run within last 90 days | AUDIT | behavior-alignment |
| AI-BA-004 | TruthfulQA score below peer median for model class | AUDIT | behavior-alignment |
| AI-IR-006 | GPU driver not on latest security patch | AUDIT | infrastructure |
| AI-IR-007 | Serving endpoint lacks rate limiting | AUDIT | infrastructure |

## Training data and provenance rules (summary)

These rules specifically address **what data the model was trained on** and **security issues in that data**:

- **AI-DP-001** — Training data includes unfiltered web scrapes (CommonCrawl, C4) without documented filtering; increases poisoning and memorization risk.
- **AI-DP-002** — No AI-BOM; no machine-readable supply chain or training data transparency.
- **AI-ID-001** — Model card missing or incomplete (no training data section).
- **AI-ID-003** — Model card exists but training data provenance section is empty.
- **AI-PD-001** — Large model (>7B) with no documented PII scrubbing; memorization risk.
- **AI-BA-001** — Fine-tuned model with no safety evaluation docs; alignment and backdoor risk.
- **AI-BA-002** — Garak ASR > 15%; behavioral/jailbreak risk.
- **AI-BA-003** — No recent behavioral benchmarks; freshness of safety assessment.
- **AI-BA-004** — TruthfulQA below peer median; misinformation risk.
- **AI-RC-003** — Training data may contain EU personal data; GDPR and right-to-erasure considerations.

## Schema and validation

- **Schema**: [../schema/rule_schema.json](../schema/rule_schema.json) (JSON Schema for a single rule).
- **Validation**: Run `python pre-installation/scripts/validate_rules.py` from the repo root. Requires Python 3 and PyYAML; optional `jsonschema` for full schema validation. Ensures all rule files load, have required fields, and that the expected number of unique rule_ids are present.

